{"data":{"logo":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":400,"height":128,"src":"/static/2b5eaa0de166a8b5faebad4955c2200c/51380/ghost-logo.png","srcSet":"/static/2b5eaa0de166a8b5faebad4955c2200c/51380/ghost-logo.png 1x"}}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<div>\n          <div\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\"\n            style=\"padding-bottom: 56.28342245989305%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1rem\"\n          >\n            <iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/xdJGTABGjd0\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen style=\"\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          \"></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<p>Dear Mother.</p>\n<p>​</p>\n<p>Have you ever stopped to think</p>\n<p>On the consequences of your reactions,</p>\n<p>On the outcome of your actions,</p>\n<p>On exactly what you want to teach the child you want to raise.</p>\n<p>​</p>\n<p>Do you want them to go out in the world and think for themselves,</p>\n<p>To bring them out of their shells,</p>\n<p>To be ready to take on the challenges,</p>\n<p>The punches life throws.</p>\n<p>Because there are a lot of those.</p>\n<p>How do you want them to think, to speak</p>\n<p>Do you want them confident or meek.</p>\n<p>Do you want to build them up to survive</p>\n<p>And thrive</p>\n<p>Once you’re not around</p>\n<p>Or do you think more about how they can support you now</p>\n<p>Support you with words no child</p>\n<p>Should ever hear out loud</p>\n<p>Every time you criticize</p>\n<p>You tell your lies</p>\n<p>You don’t apologize</p>\n<p>Be aware that your child is listening</p>\n<p>Is taking it all in</p>\n<p>Because what a child sees, he or she will do</p>\n<p>Because actions speak louder than words,</p>\n<p>It’s true.</p>\n<p>Which has more of an impact, you think?</p>\n<p>When you tell your child not to make the same mistakes you did</p>\n<p>Or when you show them how to be</p>\n<p>How to live and breathe how you believe</p>\n<p>In accordance with what you truly know is alright.</p>\n<p>That is a parent’s plight.</p>\n<p>But it should be an easy answer, right?</p>\n<p>Dear Mother</p>\n<p>Do you ever question?</p>\n<p>What you are teaching?</p>\n<p>What kind of example you are preaching?</p>\n<p>Do you want to encourage your children to stand tall</p>\n<p>To solve their own problems,</p>\n<p>To get through it all.</p>\n<p>Or do you want them to forever have your voice in their head</p>\n<p>Telling them they are better off dead</p>\n<p>That they will never amount to anything with or without you.</p>\n<p>No matter what they try or do.</p>\n<p>That the only time they are doing good is when they obey every word you say</p>\n<p>And don’t question.</p>\n<p>Your intention.</p>\n<p>Or your unjust suspension.</p>\n<p>Your hypocrisy, your own deeds,</p>\n<p>If they go against what you speak.</p>\n<p>Do you really believe</p>\n<p>Dear Mother</p>\n<p>That you have nothing to do with their pain?</p>\n<p>You, closest to them</p>\n<p>And then</p>\n<p>They are responsible for making you happy, for your happiness?</p>\n<p>To expect them to pretend and lend</p>\n<p>Themselves even when things aren’t okay, just to save</p>\n<p>Your feelings?</p>\n<p>But then you won’t do the same for them?</p>\n<p>You expect them to be</p>\n<p>The saviour to your negativity,</p>\n<p>Pain, and past trauma.</p>\n<p>And they are just supposed to come back and take it.</p>\n<p>Because they are your child?</p>\n<p>And they are ungrateful?</p>\n<p>Selfish? Despicable?</p>\n<p>That when you blame it all on the friends they choose</p>\n<p>And every game that they lose</p>\n<p>It’s because they didn’t listen to you</p>\n<p>To the standards you hold them to</p>\n<p>Even when you don’t do</p>\n<p>Those things yourself.</p>\n<p>Do you want to breed fear and pain from your position above.</p>\n<p>Is that really what you want?</p>\n<p>To choose power over love?</p>\n<p>Have you ever stopped to think</p>\n<p>That maybe your child is a separate entity from you</p>\n<p>That they have their own mind</p>\n<p>That maybe they know themselves better</p>\n<p>That just because you are their mother</p>\n<p>It doesn’t give you the excuse to silence them.</p>\n<p>That because they are the child and you the parent</p>\n<p>That doesn’t mean you always know better,</p>\n<p>That whatever</p>\n<p>They say</p>\n<p>That you don’t agree with, they may not be wrong,</p>\n<p>Insane?</p>\n<p>That it doesn’t give you a free ticket to hate,</p>\n<p>To berate</p>\n<p>To humiliate</p>\n<p>To sedate their feelings, to numb them out of existence.</p>\n<p>Just because you don’t like that they sometimes have negative feelings.</p>\n<p>It doesn’t give you the excuse</p>\n<p>To verbally abuse.</p>\n<p>Dear Mother</p>\n<p>Do you ever stop to think if it’s right to respond to sadness with anger</p>\n<p>To teach a child that when they don’t do exactly what you say they are unloved and a failure</p>\n<p>That everything they do</p>\n<p>Is only ever a product of you</p>\n<p>When they do well?</p>\n<p>Don’t you want your child to succeed with or without you</p>\n<p>Or do you want them to doubt everything they do.</p>\n<p>But when you choose</p>\n<p>To raise them to hate</p>\n<p>How can you expect them to love?</p>\n<p>You say you give them everything</p>\n<p>Materially, physically.</p>\n<p>But everything you buy and provide</p>\n<p>Means nothing when you are divided</p>\n<p>Dear Mother.</p>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n          "},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"],"style":"padding-bottom: 56.28342245989305%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1rem"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n   